    "By addressing these areas, stakeholders can ensure that the digitization of legal systems contributes to building more equitable, efficient, and inclusive legal environments in developing countries.Therefore, while the digitization of legal systems in developing countries presents both opportunities and challenges, the benefits far outweigh the difficulties.",
    "Countries like India, Kenya, Brazil, and Rwanda have demonstrated that with the right investment in technology, infrastructure, and training, legal systems can become more efficient, transparent, and accessible to all citizens.",
    "However, sustained efforts are needed to address the digital divide, improve digital literacy, and ensure that new technologies like blockchain are integrated in a secure and equitable manner.",
